1
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:21,290
ASTEROID BLUES

2
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:08,860
Hey, Spike!

3
00:03:10,170 --> 00:03:11,740
It’s ready!

4
00:03:11,740 --> 00:03:14,400
I’m just about done myself.
What’s cooking?

5
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:16,380
Special “beef with bell peppers.”
Qing-jiao-rou-si.

6
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:28,880
Asimov Solensan.
This is our next target.

7
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:31,660
Hey, Jet…

8
00:03:31,660 --> 00:03:35,300
He’s a high-end of the syndicate
that deals all around the asteroids.

9
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:37,560
About this Qing-jiao-rou-si…

10
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:41,070
The guy’s name is Asimov Solensan.
Weren’t you listening to me?!

11
00:03:41,070 --> 00:03:43,700
You don’t call a meatless
“beef with bell peppers”…

12
00:03:43,740 --> 00:03:46,570
…“beef with bell peppers”… do you?

13
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:49,740
Yes, you do.

14
00:03:49,780 --> 00:03:51,040
No, you don’t!

15
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:53,510
You do when you’re broke!

16
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:56,520
What happened to the 1 million woolongs
we got as bounty from that last guy?!

17
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,810
The repair bill for
the plane you wrecked…

18
00:03:59,850 --> 00:04:02,410
…and the repair bill
for the shop you trashed…

19
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:05,050
…and the medical bill
of the cop you injured…

20
00:04:05,130 --> 00:04:06,620
Killed all the dough!

21
00:04:08,810 --> 00:04:14,110
Three days ago, there was a shootout
between his group and an enemy syndicate.

22
00:04:14,150 --> 00:04:16,710
He killed his own men and took off.

23
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:21,000
They say he’s hiding
with his woman in Tijuana.

24
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:23,540
That’s a place for nobodies to go.

25
00:04:23,580 --> 00:04:26,740
Despite being a nobody,
he’s worth 2.5 million.

26
00:04:26,780 --> 00:04:28,370
Don’t feel like it.

27
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:31,050
Tijuana… The beef there…

28
00:04:31,050 --> 00:04:32,850
…is really tasty…

29
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:38,090
<i>“Attention, please.</i>
<i>We will soon arrive at the gate.”</i>

30
00:04:38,090 --> 00:04:40,560
<i>“We look forward to serving you again.”</i>

31
00:04:52,870 --> 00:04:57,210
<i>Please line up single file at</i>
<i>the tollbooth after clearing the gate.</i>

32
00:04:57,840 --> 00:05:01,910
<i>Please pass by after switching</i>
<i>the credit sensors to debit mode.</i>

33
00:05:15,210 --> 00:05:18,440
I’ll head over after
hitting the cops for clues.

34
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:22,350
<i>Then I’ll try seeing old man Bull.</i>

35
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:25,720
<i>Can you trust that old guy?</i>

36
00:05:53,850 --> 00:05:55,550
Such an easygoing song.

37
00:06:18,010 --> 00:06:19,980
Thief!

38
00:06:29,350 --> 00:06:31,620
This again? Goddamn sonofabitch!

39
00:06:32,290 --> 00:06:35,590
Man, you’re totally ripping me off,
but do ya realize…

40
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:37,990
…the reason you can
live here is because…

41
00:06:38,030 --> 00:06:41,900
…I dug that gate with
all my might, ya hear?

42
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:45,210
This again.
You always say that when you lose.

43
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:48,550
We all dug the gate together, remember?

44
00:06:48,590 --> 00:06:52,250
That we did.
We dug like there was no tomorrow…

45
00:06:52,290 --> 00:06:54,688
Goddamn idiot sonofabitch!

46
00:07:09,110 --> 00:07:10,540
Gimme a beer.

47
00:07:10,580 --> 00:07:13,170
And I’ll have a Bloody Mary.

48
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:20,430
I got vodka, but unfortunately
I’m out of tomato juice.

49
00:07:20,470 --> 00:07:23,560
I’m sure there’s one can
in the back room…

50
00:07:25,140 --> 00:07:26,840
I’ll take a look.

51
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:39,620
Top-notch “Red-Eye.”

52
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:41,250
You’d know, as a buyer, right?

53
00:07:41,290 --> 00:07:44,120
Can it be… “Bloody-Eye”?

54
00:07:52,620 --> 00:07:55,380
Prove to me that it’s the real thing.

55
00:08:20,180 --> 00:08:22,817
Keep those eyes open!

56
00:09:27,810 --> 00:09:30,840
This is dandy,
but you got anything to eat?

57
00:09:35,690 --> 00:09:36,660
I see…

58
00:09:39,930 --> 00:09:44,330
The red-eyed coyote will appear
at the north end of town.

59
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,390
That is what I see.

60
00:09:46,430 --> 00:09:48,460
A red-eyed coyote, huh…

61
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:51,100
You, “Swimming Bird.”

62
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:53,500
You shall meet a woman.

63
00:09:53,540 --> 00:09:56,480
You shall be targeted
by that woman…

64
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,747
And then… death.

65
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:01,470
Again. I see.

66
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:02,880
“Again”?

67
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:07,120
I’ve already died once.
Got killed by a woman.

68
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:10,320
You take women too lightly.

69
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:12,350
Catch ya later.

70
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:17,974
May he be blessed by Wakantanka.

71
00:10:28,710 --> 00:10:32,840
Presidente?
I’ll have a glass on the house.

72
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:41,610
Damn. Asimov sure lost his head.

73
00:10:41,650 --> 00:10:45,960
No shit. We gotta do something
before the cops start moving.

74
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,930
Ya wanna leave it up to the cops?

75
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:51,450
He IS using those eye drops.
There’s no way we can win.

76
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:56,130
I’m tellin’ ya, we got nothin’ if
we don’t get that “Bloody-Eye” back.

77
00:10:56,170 --> 00:10:57,305
But, man!

78
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:59,830
Hey.

79
00:11:02,610 --> 00:11:05,100
Can you give me the specifics?

80
00:11:13,490 --> 00:11:16,080
Man, I’m hungry…

81
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:20,520
You, too?

82
00:12:00,330 --> 00:12:02,530
It’s better to leave the water running.

83
00:12:06,370 --> 00:12:08,670
Or it’ll clog.

84
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:30,090
Oh, I’m sorry!

85
00:12:34,770 --> 00:12:36,630
Thank you…

86
00:12:37,170 --> 00:12:38,470
Um…

87
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:45,050
…l’f soffy.

88
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:48,190
Ew! I don’t want that anymore!
You can have it!

89
00:12:49,280 --> 00:12:51,580
Lukfy!

90
00:12:57,920 --> 00:12:59,260
I’m really sorry, honest.

91
00:12:59,260 --> 00:13:01,230
Felt like my stomach was
going to be glued to my back.

92
00:13:08,070 --> 00:13:09,360
Nice fighter.

93
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,870
It’s an old model.

94
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:12,600
She’s been with me for over ten years.

95
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:15,130
Looks like you’ve gotten
a lot of use out of it.

96
00:13:15,170 --> 00:13:17,940
I travel around a lot.

97
00:13:17,980 --> 00:13:20,500
I’m actually a wandering performer.

98
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:25,130
I can’t tell if you’re
for real or just joking.

99
00:13:25,170 --> 00:13:26,760
A lot of people say that about me.

100
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:29,080
Been to Mars yet?

101
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:31,020
I was born on Mars.

102
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:33,490
They have everything there.

103
00:13:33,530 --> 00:13:38,230
Unlike here, Mars has lots
of people, lots of things…

104
00:13:38,260 --> 00:13:41,070
They must live happily there.

105
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:43,040
Only the rich.

106
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:46,660
Then I’m sure we’ll be happy there.

107
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:54,930
You planning on escaping to Mars?

108
00:13:54,930 --> 00:13:54,980
Running away…
but how far can you go?
You planning on escaping to Mars?

109
00:13:54,980 --> 00:13:58,230
Running away…
but how far can you go?

110
00:13:58,270 --> 00:13:59,790
Who are you?

111
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:01,960
An old-fashioned cowboy.

112
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:04,170
A bounty hunter?

113
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:05,800
Good call.

114
00:14:06,580 --> 00:14:08,700
You’re not going to catch us?

115
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:11,440
Your buddy seems to be pretty ill.

116
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:14,880
I don’t deal with weakened nobodies.

117
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,337
Wise decision.

118
00:14:19,110 --> 00:14:20,400
You are the nobody!

119
00:14:27,010 --> 00:14:28,740
Asimov! That’s enough!

120
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:43,590
Adios, cowboy.

121
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:58,046
Why did you stop me?

122
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:02,210
I coulda killed him in one second.

123
00:15:02,250 --> 00:15:04,880
You’re tired.
If you do this anymore…

124
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:08,380
He was young and attractive.

125
00:15:09,820 --> 00:15:13,880
I was waiting so long for
you to come pick me up.

126
00:15:14,830 --> 00:15:18,350
I can finally escape the
low life I’ve had here.

127
00:15:19,170 --> 00:15:21,986
I can finally live happily on Mars…

128
00:15:34,010 --> 00:15:35,950
A nap. How peaceful.

129
00:15:36,380 --> 00:15:37,610
I had a good dream.

130
00:15:37,650 --> 00:15:39,550
That’s great.

131
00:15:39,590 --> 00:15:43,390
Then you can see the rest of
that dream on the Bebop.

132
00:15:43,460 --> 00:15:45,360
I’m giving up on this one.

133
00:15:45,390 --> 00:15:47,830
It’s impossible to catch him.

134
00:15:47,860 --> 00:15:50,120
There’s no way we can win.

135
00:15:50,260 --> 00:15:54,130
When Asimov left his syndicate,
he snuck something out with him.

136
00:15:54,170 --> 00:15:59,600
The top-end stuff of all the illegal
eye drops that the syndicate makes.

137
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:04,080
He took off with all of the drops,
so the group is in a mess.

138
00:16:04,110 --> 00:16:07,310
They wanna catch him,
but all they get back are corpses.

139
00:16:07,350 --> 00:16:09,540
Because Asimov is using it…

140
00:16:09,580 --> 00:16:12,980
The eye drops known as “Bloody-Eye.”

141
00:16:13,020 --> 00:16:15,350
They’re planning on going to Mars.

142
00:16:15,390 --> 00:16:16,380
Mars?

143
00:16:16,460 --> 00:16:18,450
But before that, they’ll sell this off.

144
00:16:18,940 --> 00:16:20,470
Hmm? That’s…

145
00:16:20,510 --> 00:16:22,740
I grabbed it from his breast pocket.

146
00:16:22,780 --> 00:16:25,040
You… met him?

147
00:16:25,350 --> 00:16:26,710
A nightmare.

148
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,380
He got you?

149
00:16:29,420 --> 00:16:33,550
The red-eyed coyote will supposedly
appear at the north end of town.

150
00:16:53,990 --> 00:16:56,622
This again? Goddamn sonofabitch!

151
00:16:57,300 --> 00:17:02,070
Man, you’re totally rippin’ me off, but do
ya realize the reason you can eat well…

152
00:17:02,070 --> 00:17:06,770
…around here is because I cultivated
the land with my buddies, ya hear?

153
00:17:06,810 --> 00:17:09,040
Yeah, and that’s us.

154
00:17:09,080 --> 00:17:10,770
That we did…

155
00:17:10,810 --> 00:17:13,510
We planted seeds like
there was no tomorrow…

156
00:17:13,550 --> 00:17:17,810
You were always planting “seeds”
of a different kind, though!

157
00:17:29,460 --> 00:17:31,490
You have any Bloody Marys?

158
00:17:31,530 --> 00:17:33,618
I only got beer.

159
00:17:33,730 --> 00:17:35,600
I’ve got tomato juice.

160
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:36,690
How much?

161
00:17:36,740 --> 00:17:39,830
300,000 woolongs.
I got 50 packs.

162
00:17:39,870 --> 00:17:41,970
15 million woolongs, eh?

163
00:17:42,010 --> 00:17:44,910
I’m in a hurry. I’ll find others
if you don’t want it.

164
00:17:45,330 --> 00:17:46,350
Show me.

165
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:52,310
Lookin’ for this?

166
00:17:53,390 --> 00:17:56,250
Hey, do you know what YOU are worth?

167
00:17:56,290 --> 00:17:57,350
What?

168
00:17:57,390 --> 00:18:00,330
Only 2.5 million woolongs.

169
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:02,690
You’re such a cheap guy.

170
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:06,220
Long time no see.

171
00:18:06,270 --> 00:18:10,070
Since when are you a buyer?
Did you give up on bounty hunting?

172
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:12,700
No thrill in cheap bounties.

173
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:16,000
Looks like you do better as a thief.

174
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:17,770
Give it back.

175
00:18:17,810 --> 00:18:19,080
Sure I will.

176
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:21,170
I owe you one!

177
00:18:36,660 --> 00:18:40,390
You trust your eyes too much!
You’re not a chameleon!

178
00:18:40,430 --> 00:18:42,560
You can’t see everywhere all at once!

179
00:19:03,540 --> 00:19:05,010
Let’s go!

180
00:19:05,710 --> 00:19:06,970
That way!

181
00:19:09,410 --> 00:19:11,310
That way! That way!

182
00:19:11,350 --> 00:19:12,750
What the hell are you?!

183
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:14,850
Don’t move!

184
00:19:15,130 --> 00:19:17,330
All right, stay still!

185
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:28,190
Idiot!

186
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:31,560
We’re doomed if these break!
Be more careful!

187
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:52,420
Sorry to keep you waiting.

188
00:19:52,420 --> 00:19:54,190
You’re late, Jet!

189
00:19:54,190 --> 00:19:55,090
Oh…

190
00:19:55,090 --> 00:19:57,094
…shit!

191
00:20:05,450 --> 00:20:07,021
Asimov.

192
00:20:33,510 --> 00:20:37,450
Stop! Doing any more is insane!
Don’t do it!

193
00:20:57,640 --> 00:21:00,500
We can’t run anymore…

194
00:21:00,540 --> 00:21:03,870
There’s no way we can get away…

195
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:26,010
Adios…

196
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:46,880
Hey, Spike, it’s ready!

197
00:22:12,510 --> 00:22:13,780
It’s ready.

198
00:22:13,780 --> 00:22:15,250
What’s cooking?

199
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:17,610
Special “beef with bell peppers.”

200
00:22:46,550 --> 00:22:51,980
Aishiteta to nageku niwa…
Too much time has passed by…

201
00:22:52,020 --> 00:22:58,320
…amarinimo toki wa sugite shimatta
…to lament that we were deeply in love.

202
00:22:58,360 --> 00:23:04,020
Mada kokoro no hokorobi wo…
The wind keeps blowing, while my heart…

203
00:23:04,060 --> 00:23:10,760
…iyasenu mama kaze ga fuiteru
…cannot heal all the tears in it.

204
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:20,010
Kawaita hitomi de dareka naite kure
Someone, cry for me with parched eyes.

205
00:23:21,610 --> 00:23:25,020
The real folk blues.

206
00:23:25,020 --> 00:23:33,430
Honto no kanashimi ga shiritai dake
I only want to know what true sadness is.

207
00:23:33,460 --> 00:23:41,060
Doro no kawa ni tsukatta…
Sitting in muddy water…

208
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:45,560
…jinsei mo waruku wa nai…
…isn’t such a bad life…

209
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:54,480
…ichido kiri de owaru nara…
…if it ends after the first time…

210
00:24:10,550 --> 00:24:11,180
COMING EPISODE

211
00:24:11,180 --> 00:24:11,640
Well, and so this program
is finally under way.
COMING EPISODE

212
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:13,550
Well, and so this program
is finally under way.

213
00:24:13,550 --> 00:24:14,880
What’s the meaning of all this?

214
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:17,188
Next week, we’re completely changing
gears to show an anime for all ages.

215
00:24:17,220 --> 00:24:18,750
Was it that kind of a story?

216
00:24:18,750 --> 00:24:20,950
—Cheerful animals wreak havoc all over!
—WHAT?!

217
00:24:20,950 --> 00:24:22,920
But Dr. Doolittle won’t
be making an appearance.

218
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,920
From little kids to the elderly,
if you love animals…

219
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:26,560
Hey, hold on now, Spike!

220
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:28,330
Everyone gather around
and watch the show!

221
00:24:28,330 --> 00:24:30,360
Is it all right to
say stuff like that?!

222
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:31,630
I’m not responsible for anything!

223
00:24:31,630 --> 00:24:33,230
But there is one favor
to ask right now.

224
00:24:33,230 --> 00:24:35,430
Good little kids should sit far
from the TV when watching the show.

225
00:24:35,430 --> 00:24:36,240
Come on…

226
00:24:36,240 --> 00:24:36,620
Stand back about a kilometer.

227
00:24:36,620 --> 00:24:37,270
STRAY DOG STRUT
Stand back about a kilometer.

228
00:24:37,270 --> 00:24:38,600
STRAY DOG STRUT
That’s too far.

229
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:39,620
STRAY DOG STRUT
800 meters then?

230
00:24:39,620 --> 00:24:39,730
800 meters then?
